THE Architects Registration Council of Nigeria has accredited the Bachelor and Master degree programme of Caleb University Imota, Lagos. A statement made available to The PUNCH by the university said the approval was communicated in a letter signed by the Registrar of ARCON, Mr Umar Murnai, based on a report of a professional visitation. It read in part, “We refer to the professional accreditation visitation to the Department of Architecture, Caleb University, Imota Lagos, held between 12th and16th April 2021, and we hereby inform you that in line with Section 9 of the Architects Registration Act CAP A19 Laws of the Federation of Nigeria 2004, the Architects Registration Council of Nigeria approves the report of the panel. “In view of the fact that the department has the acceptable physical infrastructure, facilities and equipment, an acceptable staff/students’ ratio and a general assessment of 77.52 per cent, the council approves the recommendation of the Bachelor of Science and Masters of Science degree programmes in architecture.” It also stated that the architecture programme had been granted accreditation by the NUC, adding that some other courses, including B.Sc. Economics; B.Sc. Political Science; B.Sc. International Relations; and BSc. Criminology, Security Studies also got NUC’s accreditation.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com